				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: WOO!!  Bards a Broke (Again)<a name="71212"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 17 04 3:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Just to summarize a few other posts, + my experiences:
<br />

<br />
A missed note, or /stopsong, &quot;Interrupts&quot; a melody... it does not &quot;stop&quot; it.  Recasting any song will play that song, then the melody picks up where it was interrupted.
<br />

<br />
Playing a blank /melody (No #'s, stop, or 0) will &quot;stop&quot; the melody, and allow songs cast once to run continously.  This also functions as /stopsong, and can be used to replace it.
<br />

<br />
For example, I use socials to cast all my songs, so I left my normal twisting songs with /stopsong in front, that way I can let /melody resume if I miss a note or get bashed, etc.  Certain songs get /melody in front, because they will rarely/never be used in a normal twist.  For me, Selo's, Harmony of Sound, and Lull.  Experimented with Mezz, decided to use /stopsong there, makes for easy melee/toggle mezzing and twisting.  
<br />

<br />
I also have a stopsong button for use with Tiny cloak, SS Boots, etc.  I changed this from /stopsong to /melody (Blank), and use it now when I need to mezz more than one mob, or want to chain mezz one mob (i.e. to interrupt gating mobs.)
<br />

<br />
Only have one /melody hot button, I prefer to use the auto-restart feature rather than burn precious hotkey space on multiple /melody commands.
<br />

<br />
Haven't tested it on raids yet, suspect I will probably still manually twist for boss mobs, at the very least.
<br />

<br />
Was nice to finish a multi-hour, 4-twist XP grind last night and not have to put an icepack on my hand.  I could even chat with the group a bit.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Cheers,
<br />
Grith</span></td>
