				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: WOO!!  Bards a Broke (Again)<a name="71322"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 20 04 5:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>all the hubbub and call of bugs for melody are just from folks being to impatient to see how the system really works.
<br />
if u are playing melody 1 2 3 4 and the song gets interrupted on say 2, u can hits song 2 again and melody will pick up from where it left off. or u can hit 3, or 4 and it will pick up from that position in the melody.
<br />
now if u get interrupted on melody and then play a song not in your current melody line up, it thinks its a new melody command and will chain melody that one song.
<br />

<br />
with the melody going the server thinks that you are casting a song everytime melody goes off, hence the standing when u try to sit. 
<br />
if u get an interruption, either restart the song and continue with your melody, or start/stop the song and continue manually.
<br />

<br />
i've not encountered a single bug or anything else that a brain and a few electrical impulses won't fix. then again i've been doing this for over 4yrs maybe i catch on faster.
<br />
</span></td>
