				<td colspan="2"><span>actually the day melody became live.. i learned to use melody.. u would use /melody 1, 2, 3, 4  and that'll twist the melody..
<br />
now i figured hmm how do i stop melody.. i tried out /melody stop and it worked.. so on mindless exp groups.. hot keys would be set up like this... wsad for movements..
<br />
1: /melody stop,  /melody 1, 2, 3
<br />
2: /melody stop
<br />
3: /melody stop, cast 1 (down time song 1 being my mana song)
<br />
4: /melody stop, /stop song, /cast 4
<br />
5: /melody stop, /stop song, /cast 5
<br />
6: /melody stop, /stop song, /cast 6
<br />
7: /melody stop, /stop song, /cast 7
<br />
8: /melody stop, /stop song, /cast 8
<br />
9: /melody stop, /stop song, /cast 9  (also combined with key &quot;e&quot;)
<br />
0: /alt activate 212, /stop attack, /stop song, /g I am Fading Aggro!  (also combined with key &quot;q&quot;)
<br />

<br />
for serious groups or raids.. i would switch to manul twisting.  since really nothing beats manual twists<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />
 
<br />
aye to refresh a lost melody list.. i either press 1 again to start the command over.. or just use my mouse and click the gem<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
PS: for you people wondering why i only twist 3 instead of 4.  my internet lags a lot.. and i get anywhere from 2%-20% loss..  so, twisting 4 in lag caues my songs to drop..  that is also why i dislike using melody commnad.. in serious lag songs don't work well in melody.</span></td>
